PN,31001
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FSnow is falling on high ground as far
OL,7,Fsouth as Dartmoor today, and a cutting
OL,8,Fwind is turning relatively modest
OL,9,Ftemperatures into something that feels
OL,10,Ffar closer to winter than spring.
OL,12,FBut the good news is a noticeable
OL,13,Fshift is just hours away, with a
OL,14,Fchange of wind direction set to bring
OL,15,Fa milder feel tomorrow.JWhy does it
OL,16,Ffeel so cold today when temperatures
OL,17,Faren't that low?
OL,19,FIt's all about that biting wind - or
OL,20,Fmore specifically, the direction of
OL,21,Fthat wind.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31002
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FIn the last week, the wind has veered
OL,7,Ffrom a very mild southeasterly
OL,8,F(dragging air in warm continental air)
OL,9,Fto a less mild southwesterly over the
OL,10,Fweekend, and now right round to a
OL,11,Fbitingly cold north to northwesterly
OL,12,F(Arctic Maritime airmass).
OL,14,FTemperatures across the UK today are
OL,15,Fwidely, though not dramatically, below
OL,16,Faverage at about 6-9C (though
OL,17,Fsignificantly below the high teens/low
OL,18,F20s of last week), but it's actually
OL,19,Fthe direction of the wind that's
OL,20,Fmaking today feel so raw.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FOften known as the 'wind chill' or,
OL,7,Fmore colloquially, the 'feels like',
OL,8,Ftemperatures of around 7C across the
OL,9,FNorthern Isles of Scotland today, for
OL,10,Fexample, feel as low as -4C or -5C.
OL,12,FElsewhere, it's the same story; the
OL,13,F'wind chill' takes up to 10C off the
OL,14,Ffeel of the temperature.
OL,16,FSo is this unusually cold for the time
OL,17,Fof year?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FNot particularly in terms of actual
OL,7,Ftemperatures, only slightly below the
OL,8,Fseasonal average in fact, but the feel
OL,9,Fof the weather is certainly much
OL,10,Fcolder than we'd expect in late March.
OL,12,FThe combination of gusty winds and
OL,13,Fwintry showers really adds that extra
OL,14,Fbite for some.JWhere is it feeling
OL,15,Fcoldest?
OL,17,FThe Northern Isles of Scotland are
OL,18,Fcertainly taking the brunt of it, but
OL,19,Fanywhere exposed to that wind will
OL,20,Fnotice how cold it feels.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31005
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FEven in towns and cities, those gusts
OL,7,Ffunnel between buildings and can catch
OL,8,Fyou off guard.
OL,10,FAreas with lying snow will always feel
OL,11,Fcolder too, so high ground across
OL,12,FWales and the Peak District northwards
OL,13,Fwill have an extra chill today.JHow
OL,14,Flong will it feel this cold?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31006
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FCertainly, the rest of today and
OL,7,Ftonight will feel pretty raw in the
OL,8,Fwind. But that wind slowly eases
OL,9,Fovernight, and skies are clearer. A
OL,10,Fcombination which will allow the real
OL,11,Ftemperatures to drop away too to
OL,12,Faround -5C in rural Scotland, around
OL,13,F-2C in parts of Wales, for example.
OL,15,FWatch out for icy stretches on
OL,16,Funtreated roads.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31007
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774476674
OL,3,CCold snap sweeps the UK, but could
OL,4,Cthat all be about to change?
OL,6,FWinds overnight and into tomorrow will
OL,7,Fnot only ease but crucially, they will
OL,8,Fchange direction too, backing from
OL,9,Fthat biting north/northwesterly to a
OL,10,Fmuch less cold west/southwesterly;
OL,11,Fdrawing in a milder tropical maritime
OL,12,Fairmass from the mid Atlantic.
OL,14,FWith fewer showers, lighter, less cold
OL,15,Fwinds and more sunshine on the cards,
OL,16,Ftomorrow will feel noticeably milder
OL,17,Fthan today, even though the actual
OL,18,Ftemperature will only lift by a degree
OL,19,For so (7-11C across the country).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
